import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='source', y='target')
    plt.title("What is the relationship between source and target?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='source', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['source'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['source'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of source?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    top_10_sources = data['source'].value_counts().head(10)
    top_10_sources_df = pd.DataFrame(top_10_sources).reset_index()
    top_10_sources_df.columns = ['source', 'count']

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='source', y='count', data=top_10_sources_df, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What are the top 10 most common source values?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Source')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(title='Top 10 Sources', labels=top_10_sources_df['source'].values, loc='upper right')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    top_10_targets = data['target'].value_counts().head(10)
    sns.barplot(x=top_10_targets.index, y=top_10_targets.values)
    plt.xlabel('Target Values')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What are the top 10 most common target values?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
